               <p>I was present when the things were found upon the prisoner.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>My three children had the small pox, one has been cut for the stone, and this has lost its sight since it has been in prison. I owed fourteen shillings for rent; I was going to my master's to borrow a few shillings to save my goods, this man met me in the street and knocked me down two or three times; he said he believed I was the person who stole his coat. I know nothing of the coat.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner called her mother and 
               <persName id="t17800913-60-person630">
